reviews.text: What a great restaurant. Lots of classic HK dishes done with Beyond Meat products. Perfect for vegans, vegetarians, or people who don't eat red meat and pork. Beyond Meats are the latest craze in mock meat around the world that taste like real meat unlike typical soy meats. My favourites were the Tan Tan Noodles which were nice and chewy and flavoured properly, and the Tom yum soup which was a thicker variant than what you are used to which was a pleasant surprise. You can also stock up on snacks, frozen foods, and other goodies here while you are at it.

Couldn’t have been more relieved to find this healthy vegan haven in the middle of the city! Fantastic options, great clean space with plenty of other eco friendly/ health/ vegan products to grab while there.It was our first time trying the famous ‘beyond burger’ and I was pleased to confirm that it does intact live up to all the hype - so delicious!

Special Promotion for Beyond Burger with 50% price off hence give it a try. Nice Burger with taste and texture similar to real meat burger. Strong Mushroom taste which covers most of the flavour. Fries is cool hence not recommended.

I always go here because I generally like going to green common for different vegan food products. The spaghetti with sausage is one of their new menu items. I personally don't really like the taste of the sausage (given the fact that I don't really enjoy fake meat) but the tomato flavor of the pasta is nice and tangy. Other food items here are pretty nice. Their 'pork chop' is quite similar to the non vegan counterpart. They also have different meatless food you can try. I personally like their salad bowls too.

To me when I went their, it's seemed that they had been using ingredients they sell in their shop when they were about to or have been off. The coconut oil they used was rancid and I had a bad after taste and sore throat after I ate their food. Great for waste reduction, not so great for paying customers

reviews.text:
lovely Shopping mall in Mong Kok. Approximately 300m from the train station

 you will find on the main sports and sports related outlets plus s variety of restaurants 
building has numerous vertical gardens which creates an outdoor feeling.  ample public spaces, seating areas areas in this multi levels mall. there are also a number of free phone charging stations.  restrooms are extremely clean. 

outlets in the mall are  logically spread out and directional signs legible displayed to assist in the navigation of the mall
a different feel to your usual mall. an easy upscale place.

Nice place to sit and have a snack. The Forest is themed after nature and aims to give you a relaxing experience in the urban concrete jungle. Sadly all the flowers and greens that decorate the place are made from plastic. The stuff that's not really good for forests... Keeping that amount of plants healthy in this environment would be impossible of course but being surrounded by plastic plants is a bit disturbing. The food and drinks are ok an priced at the higher end. Definitely a nice experience
Stylish & model mall at Mongkok, not much choice of shops though. But they have several restaurant there worth trying.
Impressive retail space with an environmental twist filled with greenery and shops with a sustainability angle. Lovely little rooftop garden on 3rd floor.
There are many shop assistants waiting to serve you which made me afraid because I just want to take a look instead of buying anything. Not good for window shopping.

reviews.text: 這是比较新的商场。在里面的商店公司，佈置擺設都很時尚美观，商品种类繁多，琳琅满目，有波鞋，运动服装和饮食店……等，是購物的好地方。(沒有相片)！
多鞋店，餐廳，空間大，行吓幾好。
旺角一流的大型商場 產品應有盡有 多間著名食肆 交通方便
